cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes improvements to data reduction algorithms for a well-known combinatorial optimization problem.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the d-Hitting Set problem is a classic problem in discrete mathematics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the size of problem kernels and the time and space complexity of the algorithms.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the d-Hitting Set problem has applications in machine learning and pattern recognition.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also less likely but possible as the d-Hitting Set problem can be formulated as a geometric problem in some cases.
